Ecological notes : very common in broad-leaved and carr woodland; also found in mixed woodland; conifer plantations and ancient pine woodland; heathland; moorland; wetlands including fens, mires, bogs, water meadows, sedge beds and riverside habitats; unimproved calcareous grassland; grounds of horticultural research station; school grounds with old poplars; garden; fixed dune grassland and scrub; coastal cliffs; open montane habitats; mining spoil heaps. Reared from dung. iii, v–x.
